claim.claim-text:
1. A method for providing a reverse air bearing surface head, comprising:
forming a return pole of a write head proximate to a read sensor;
forming a write gap over the return pole;
forming a first write pole extending from a yoke region toward an air bearing surface and recessed therefrom a predetermined distance
forming a second write pole, coupled to the first write pole, between the first write pole and the return pole; and
shaping the second write pole to form a pole tip having a trapezoidal shaped air bearing surface with first and second angled sides of the second pole to form a first pole tip width wider along the write gap than a second pole tip width distal to the write gap and to form a third angled side extending from the air bearing surface to the first write pole providing a first pole thickness at a recessed region wider than a second pole thickness at the pole tip at the air bearing surface.
